# Auto push after changes

When you finish making code changes in this project:

1. Commit the changes with a clear message (unless the user explicitly says not to commit).
2. Push to `origin/main` immediately after a successful commit.
3. Briefly confirm the push succeeded (commit hash + that Vercel will auto-deploy).

Do not leave completed work only on local disk. The user expects GitHub and Vercel to stay in sync after every change session.
